verbose_text: One of the larger unknowns in predictions of sea level rise over the next century stems from the potential for rapid dynamic collapse of ice sheets, which could increase sea level rise to over 2 m by 2100 (Allison et al. 2009, Ritz et al. 2015, Kopp et al. 2017, Slater and Shepherd 2018, Bamber et al. 2019).
